      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Yes; we can detect it by running fdatasync() on a directory that we know exists and observing the result. I'd be glad to rewrite it into an autoconf run-program, but things like includes are disparate across platforms for this and a generic program would likely only be functional on tested platforms. A check for the name of the platform (programmed logic) rather than detected behaviour was simpler andâI figuredâperhaps less effort and less prone to failure modes. I'd hate to have corrected this behaviour on NetBSD and then made configure non-functional on a platform I don't currently have access to. :-)",
      "commit_id" : "58702a5c49015e9a01062ac6e8b0440e7f2348d3",
